class Solution {
    public int rearrangeCharacters(String s, String target) {
        int[] sCount = new int[26];
        int[] targetCount = new int[26];

        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            sCount[c - 'a']++;
        }

        for (char c : target.toCharArray()) {
            targetCount[c - 'a']++;
        }

        int maxCopies = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        for (int i = 0; i < 26; i++) {
            if (targetCount[i] > 0) {
                maxCopies = Math.min(maxCopies, sCount[i] / targetCount[i]);
            }
        }

        return maxCopies;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n + m)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution counts the frequency of characters in both strings, then determines the maximum number of copies of the target string that can be formed by dividing the count of each character in s by its count in target and taking the minimum of these ratios.
